    "body": "The current version of the Steam runtime provides a build of GCC 9 that does not include a dynamic libgcc at all, so this would be nice for being able to use a consistent, modern gcc build in that environment.\r\n\r\n@nehaljwani's workaround, slightly tweaked to replace `-lgcc_eh -lc` with `-lgcc`, got steam runtime gcc 9 working for me.",
